title: Selwood walks out on Eagles
text:
AFL trades 2015: Scott Selwood confirms he’ll seek move to Geelong after leaving West Coast Eagles Chris Robinson PerthNow AFL trades 2015: Scott Selwood confirms he’ll seek move to Geelong after leaving West Coast Eagles Chris Robinson PerthNow Adelaide Crows name Don Pyke as new coach 0:30 
AFL: The Adelaide Crows have announced former Eagles stoppages coach Don Pyke as their new head coach, replacing the late Phil Walsh. October 9th 2015 2 hours ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/AFL/News/ 
SCOTT Selwood has officially played his last game at West Coast, with the vice-captain confirming he wants to join his brother Joel at Geelong. 
West Coast released a statement on Friday afternoon saying Selwood had informed the club of his desire to return to Victoria. 
Selwood played 135 games for the Eagles but was left out of the side’s Grand Final side last week. 
West Coast issued a brief three-sentence statement, saying Selwood had nominated the Cats as his preferred destination under the league’s restricted free agency process. 
The WA club said it would “now commence consideration of its next step”. 
The announcement came just hours before West Coast’s Worsfold Medal count for the club’s best-and-fairest award - an honour that Selwood snared just three years ago. Other Stories
